Interface Element

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CellReference, Function, Sum1, Sum2, Value
    public interface Element
    Interface defining an element capable of being processed by a SpreadSheet. All methods have to be implemented but the toString() method which is optional. The string returned by the value() method should NOT throw any exceptions if passed to Double.parseDouble(String).
    Author:
    Grupo I, Turma A, POO 2018

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      java.lang.String toString()
      Returns a visual text representation of this element.
      java.util.TreeSet<Position> usedBy()
      Method that returns the cell's Positions of a SpreadSheet this element is being used on.
      java.util.TreeSet<Position> using()
      Method that returns the cell's Positions of a SpreadSheet this element is using to calculate its value().
      java.lang.String value()
      Method defining the numerical value of this element.

    • Method Detail

      • value

        java.lang.String value()
        Method defining the numerical value of this element. The string returned by this method must be either a valid integer or floating point number.
        Returns:
        string containing the numeric value of this element

      • using

        java.util.TreeSet<Position> using()
        Method that returns the cell's Positions of a SpreadSheet this element is using to calculate its value(). It's possible for this method to return an empty TreeSet, if it doesn't depend on any cells.
        Returns:
        the cell's positions of a SpreadSheet this element is using

      • usedBy

        java.util.TreeSet<Position> usedBy()
        Method that returns the cell's Positions of a SpreadSheet this element is being used on. It's possible for this method to return an empty TreeSet, if it not being used by any other cells.
        Returns:
        the cell's positions of a SpreadSheet this element is being used by

      • toString

        java.lang.String toString()
        Returns a visual text representation of this element. (Optional)
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a visual text representation of this element
